<h2><span class="badge bg-warning">Learning Hebrew</span></h2>

<p class="h5">
	<strong>Why Learn Hebrew?</strong>
	<br />There are several good reasons to learn a little Hebrew:

	@* <ul class="fa-ul size16"> This doesnt work      *@
	<ul class="fa-ul lead">
		<li><i class="fa-li fas fa-caret-right text-warning"></i>In your personal Bible study, knowing some of the Hebrew words from which the English words were translated can often lead to additional insights.</li>
		<li><i class="fa-li fas fa-caret-right text-warning"></i>Knowing a little Hebrew can be of great help if you ever travel to Israel.</li>
	</ul>
</p>

<div class="card card-body bg-light">
	<h4>Consider this verse found in the New King Jame Version which reads</h4>
	<blockquote class="blockquote">
		For then I will restore to the peoples a pure language, that they all may call on the name of the Lord, to serve Him with one accord.
		<small>Zephaniah 3:9</small>
	</blockquote>

	<p class="h5">
		Do you suppose that the "pure language" might be Hebrew?<br />
		<a href="https://myhebrewbible.com/Hebrew/Zepc3v8"
			 class="btn btn-primary btn-sm float-end" target="_blank">
			<span class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></span> Learn More...
		</a>
	</p>

	<br /><br />

	<img src="@Constants.Blobs.Link("Alephbet.jpg")" alt="Hebrew Alephbet" class="img-fluid rounded" style="margin:auto" />

</div>

<h2 class="mt-3"><span class="badge bg-warning">Hebrew Basics</span></h2>

<p class="h5">
	There are many tools on-line to help you learn the <b>alphabet</b> and <b>how to count.</b>  Here are just a few:
	<br>
</p>
<ul class="lead">
	<li>Animated <a href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UiCzoTs1AdE" target="_blank">Hebrew Alephbet song</a> on YouTube</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.jewfaq.org/alephbet.htm" target="_blank">Concise Reference Document</a> from Judaism 101</li>
	<li>Cute video of people from 1 to 100 <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7WwQL6hr02A" target="_blank">speaking their age in Hebrew</a></li>
	<li>The website <a href="http://hebrew4christians.com" target="_blank"> Hebrew4Christians </a> is a great source for all sorts of learning and teaching aids.  This <a href="http://www.hebrew4christians.com/Grammar/Unit_One/Homeschool/homeschool.html" target="_blank"> page </a> in particular is useful for those just starting out.</li>
</ul>

