<p>
	<BibleQuote Cite="Luke 24:27">
		<p class="fs-5 text-primary">
			Then beginning with Moses and with all the prophets, He explained to them the things concerning Himself in all the Scriptures.
		</p>
	</BibleQuote>
</p>

<p class="lead">
	Listed below are some of the Scriptures in the Tanakh (Old Testament) that Yeshua probably used when speaking with these two men on the road to Emmaus.
</p>

<div class="row">
	<div class="col-sm-3">

		<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 1))">
			Genesis 49:10
		</button>
		<blockquote class="blockquote">
			<sup>10</sup> The scepter shall not depart from Judah,<br />
			Nor the ruler’s staff from between his feet,<br />
			Until Shiloh comes*,<br />
			And to him shall be the obedience of the peoples.<br /><br />
			* Or <i>Until he comes to Shiloh</i>; or <i>Until he comes to whom it belongs</i><br /><br />
			<small><b>Genesis 49:10</b></small>
		</blockquote>

	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-3">
		<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 2))">
			Deuteronomy 18:15
		</button>
		<blockquote class="blockquote">
			<sup>15</sup> The LORD your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among you, from your countrymen, you shall listen to him.
			<small><b>Deuteronomy 18:15</b></small>
		</blockquote>
	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-3">
		<div class="card card-body bg-light">

			<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 3))">
				Isaiah 7:14
			</button>
			<blockquote class="blockquote">
				<sup>14</sup> Therefore the Lord Himself will give you a sign: Behold, a virgin will be with child and bear a son, and she will call His name Immanuel.
				<small><b>Isaiah 7:14</b></small>
			</blockquote>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="col-sm-3">
		<button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-sm" @onclick="@(e => ToggleVersePopupClick(IsCollapsed, 4))">
			Isaiah 9:6-7
		</button>
